CHANGES_REQUIRED

- P2 [ui/backend/services/meshing_gmsh/gmsh_runner.py:139,234] `gmsh.merge(str(stl_path))` is still behind the generic plain-`Exception` relabel. If the STL still exists but the host hits a read-side backend fault (`EACCES`, `EIO`, unreadable mount), the fallback at lines 249-257 passes and the error is still converted to `GmshMeshGenerationError` -> `gmsh_diverged` 422. Verbatim suggested fix: `Wrap gmsh.merge() in its own try/except, mirroring gmsh.write(), and normalize host read-side faults to FileNotFoundError/OSError before the generic geometry catch-all runs.`

- P2 [ui/backend/services/meshing_gmsh/to_foam.py:157] `_make_tarball(case_host_dir)` is only normalized for `FileNotFoundError`. Other host filesystem faults during tarball build/read (`PermissionError`, `ENOSPC`, `EIO`) still escape as raw 500s with no `GmshToFoamError` contract. Verbatim suggested fix: `Broaden the tarball-build guard to catch OSError around _make_tarball(case_host_dir) and raise GmshToFoamError("failed to build gmshToFoam tarball ...").`

- P2 [ui/backend/services/meshing_gmsh/to_foam.py:233] Host-side `polyMesh` copyback is still outside the structured error contract: `polyMesh_host.parent.mkdir(...)`, `_extract_tarball(...)`, and the subsequent host-side directory walk can raise `OSError`/`tarfile.TarError` and escape as raw 500s. Verbatim suggested fix: `Wrap the host-side polyMesh materialization/validation block in except (OSError, tarfile.TarError) and raise GmshToFoamError("failed to materialize polyMesh on host ...").`


